(29, 1, '2015-07-14 07:14:07', '2015-07-14 07:14:07', '<section class="main">\r\n<!-- ///////////////////// about-ipi starts ///////////////////// -->\r\n<section class="about-ipi">\r\n	<div class="container">\r\n		\r\n		<!-- ///////////////////// middle-title starts ///////////////////// -->\r\n		<div class="row2 trans-6 middle-title">\r\n			<div class="row">\r\n				<div class="col-xs-12">\r\n					<h1 class="section-title">About the Index of Public Integrity</h1>\r\n				</div>\r\n			</div><!-- /.row -->\r\n		</div><!-- /.trans-6 -->\r\n		<!-- ///////////////////// middle-title ends ///////////////////// -->\r\n\r\n		<!-- ///////////////////// top-content starts ///////////////////// -->\r\n		<div class="row2 trans-5 with-padding">\r\n			<div class="row">\r\n				<div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 text">\r\n					<p>\r\n						<span class="bold">The Index of Public Integrity (IPI)</span> assesses a country''s overall capacity to control corruption at both state and society level. As many studies in the field suggest, establishing effective control of corruption requires much more than the mere adoption of specific institutions and strict legal regulations. It is rather an outcome of a complex mechanism including many factors which aim to enhance transparency, accountability and oversight.\r\n					</p>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 text">\r\n					<p>\r\n						IPI therefore combines various dimensions of this mechanism. The index not only highly correlates with the World Bank''s measure on control of corruption but also with several other corruption indicators. In contrast to merely perception-based measures of governance, <span class="bold">IPI</span> allows to trace back a country''s performance to specific actionable components that can help policy makers to identify reform areas for improvement.\r\n					</p>\r\n				</div>\r\n			</div><!-- /.row -->\r\n		</div><!-- /.trans-5 -->\r\n		<!-- ///////////////////// top-content ends ///////////////////// -->\r\n\r\n		<!-- ///////////////////// middle-title starts ///////////////////// -->\r\n		<div class="row2 trans-6 middle-title">\r\n			<div class="row">\r\n				<div class="col-xs-12">\r\n					<h1 class="section-title">The IPI consists of the following six components:</h1>\r\n				</div>\r\n			</div><!-- /.row -->\r\n		</div><!-- /.trans-6 -->\r\n		<!-- ///////////////////// middle-title ends ///////////////////// -->\r\n\r\n		<!-- ///////////////////// bottom-content starts ///////////////////// -->\r\n		<div class="row component-row">\r\n			<div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 col-lg-2 text-center component">\r\n				<div class="trans-4">\r\n					<div class="icon">\r\n						<img src="<?php bloginfo(''stylesheet_directory''); ?>/img/icn/judicial-independence.png" alt="Judicial independence" title="Judicial independence" />\r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div class="trans-4 text">\r\n					<h4>JUDICIAL INDEPENDENCE</h4>\r\n					<p>\r\n						captures the extent of impartial and non-corrupt judiciary system that constitutes legal constraints on government power and is thus a key element of an effective control of corruption. The data stems from the Global Competitiveness Database developed by the World Economic Forum.\r\n					</p>\r\n				</div><!-- /.trans-4 -->\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 col-lg-2 text-center component">\r\n				<div class="trans-4">\r\n					<div class="icon">\r\n						<img src="<?php bloginfo(''stylesheet_directory''); ?>/img/icn/administrative-simplicity.png" alt="Administrative simplicity" title="Administrative simplicity" />\r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div class="trans-4 text">\r\n					<h4>ADMINISTRATIVE SIMPLICITY</h4>\r\n					<p>\r\n						measures the extent of domestic bureaucratic regulations. Excessive administrative burden and regulations open doors for discretion and red tape thereby resulting in a high risk of corruption. The component is constructed combining the average number of procedures and time needed to start a business and pay corporate taxes. The data stems from the Doing Business dataset.\r\n					</p>\r\n				</div><!-- /.trans-4 -->\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 col-lg-2 text-center component">\r\n				<div class="trans-4">\r\n					<div class="icon">\r\n						<img src="<?php bloginfo(''stylesheet_directory''); ?>/img/icn/trade-openness.png" alt="Trade openness" title="Trade openness" />\r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div class="trans-4 text">\r\n					<h4>TRADE OPENNESS</h4>\r\n					<p>\r\n						measures the extent of regulations concerning a country''s external economic activities. The less restricted the economic transactions of a country with the rest of the world are, the less room there is for administrative discretion. It combines the trade-weighted average tariff rate with the average number of procedures and time for exporting and importing. The data comes from the World Development Indicators and Doing Business datasets.\r\n					</p>\r\n				</div><!-- /.trans-4 -->\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 col-lg-2 text-center component">\r\n				<div class="trans-4">\r\n					<div class="icon">\r\n						<img src="<?php bloginfo(''stylesheet_directory''); ?>/img/icn/budget-transparency.png" alt="Budget transparency" title="Budget transparency" />\r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div class="trans-4 text">\r\n					<h4>BUDGET TRANSPARENCY</h4>\r\n					<p>\r\n						measures the overall extent and the quality of public accessibility of a central government''s budget at its different stages of implementation - from a draft proposal to audit reports - in order to provide control mechanism for discretionary public spending. The component is based on the Open Budget Index provided by the International Budget Partnership.\r\n					</p>\r\n				</div><!-- /.trans-4 -->\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 col-lg-2 text-center component">\r\n				<div class="trans-4">\r\n					<d